    "For example, we preferred unbiased Hedge's g over biased Cohen's d, and carried out nonparametric trim-and-fill analysis of the full sample in addition to Egger's test and fail-safe N calculations (see online Appendix for the list of deviations from pre-registration).",
    "Our coding resulted in 531 effect sizes.",
    "Our search identified 57 studies which represent 40 unique databases (Table 1).",
    "The oldest data in the study were drawn from 1982 (Coleman & Hoffer, 1987; Willms, 1985).",
    "The most recent data in the sample were from 2020 (Hanif et al., 2020)."
